      <description>&lt;p&gt;Emojis can be enabled in various ways in the Hugo project.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/functions/emojify/&#34; title=&#34;emojify&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; class=&#34; exturl&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;code&gt;emojify&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/a&gt;The method can be called directly in the template, or use [Inline Shortcodes](&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates#inline&#34; title=&#34;https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates#inline&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; class=&#34; exturl&#34;&gt;&#xA;    https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates#inline&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/a&gt; -shortcodes).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To use emojis globally, you need to &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/getting-started/configuration/&#34; title=&#34;configure&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; class=&#34; exturl&#34;&gt;&#xA;    configure&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/a&gt; them on your website set &lt;code&gt;enableEmoji&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt;,Then you can directly enter the emoji code in the article.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
